      "span_text": "The seizures were staged by behavioral analysis using a modification of Racine's criteria [CITATION_1] , as follows: stage I, immobilization, eye blinking, twitching of vibrissae and mouth movements; stage II, head nodding, often accompanied by facial clonus; stage III, forelimb clonus; stage IV, rearing; stage V, rearing, falling and generalized convulsions."
